title: D2_N_Library1
---
You walk to Nancy, she sits in a cozy corner, with warm lights, a bench sofa with a table connected.
{$playerName}: Hi Nancy. Do you mind if I sit here?
    <<SetMood "Nancy neutral">>
Nancy: If you want. 
She looks at you suspiciously
{$playerName}: What are you studying for?
Nancy: Biology 3.
{$playerName}: Isn't that for third years?
      <<SetMood "Nancy angry">>
Nancy: Yeah? *looks at you like you’re stupid*
{$playerName}: *Ah she is smart smart.*
      <<SetMood "Nancy hide">>
You take your seat next to her. Opening your books as you begin studying.
15 minutes passes.
{$playerName}: *Damn this question is hard.*
    -> Look it up in the book. 
        You feel Nancy giving you a pouty glare.
            <<SetMood "Nancy angry">>
        Nancy: You know it’s better to ask for help before looking it up.
        {$playerName}: I didn’t wanna bother you. You looked concentrated.
             <<SetMood "Nancy neutral">>
        Nancy: *mumbels* I wouldn't mind helping. *she looks down at her book again*
              <<SetMood "Nancy hide">>
    -> Just give up. 
        After staring at your books for a few seconds you close them and push them to the side as you take up your phone to play a game.
             <<SetMood "Nancy angry">>
        Nancy: You know this is a study period. Not game period. *she looks at you disapproving*
        {$playerName}: Sorry… *glare awkwardly*
        Nancy: If you’re just gonna play you can leave. *As she points with her eyes to the door*
        You mumble something in confusion as you quickly pack your bags to get out of there.
        Leaving you see Nancy giving you a nasty glare from above her glasses before going back to her book.
<<wait 2>>
[Cafeteria] After getting your food from the lunch lady, you look out to see Cassie sitting alone at a table upset about something. 
You begin walking towards her when you hear a girl shout.
Sasha: {$playerName}! Come and sit here! *she points to the seat next to her and her friends*
    -> You turn away from the loud table and walk toward Cassie.
        She looks up as you approach.
        {$playerName}: Mind if I sit?
        Cassie: Oh! Yeah, of course. I mean— it’s not assigned seating or anything.
        You sit.
        There’s a small pause.
        {$playerName}: You seem quieter than usual.
        She shrugs, poking at her food.
        Cassie: Just thinking, I guess.
        Her smile this time is softer. More genuine.
        Across the room, Sasha notices you didn’t come.
        She leans back in her chair, watching briefly, unreadable.
    -> You pivot and head toward Sasha’s table.
        She grins as you approach.
        Sasha: Took you long enough.
        You sit beside her, close enough that your shoulders brush.
        {$playerName}: Didn’t know there were tryouts.
        Sasha: There aren’t. I scout.
        Her teammates snicker.
        Teammate: Careful, she gets intense.
        Sasha: Only when I plan on winning.
        She deliberately bumps your knee under the table.
        Across the cafeteria, Cassie lowers her gaze back to her tray.
        No expression, no reaction. Just quiet.
    <<wait 1>>
    END OF DEMO
